alternatives.transcript: palmer is a sixty two year old female presenting with dyspnea chest pain and orthopnea following a cold that began two weeks ago the patient states she is unable to exercise due to the dyspnea with and which occurs with slight activity patient takes ten milligrams of lisinopril qd for hypertension and states she had a routine cardiac cath one year ago no known drug allergies alcohol or drug use were reported patient admits to an eight pound weight gain over the past two weeks with heart palpitations heart rate was one ten o two was ninety one respiratory rate was twenty pulse was one ten bp was one thirty over ninety and temp was normal physical exam findings were positive for jvd a laterally displaced pmi bibasilar rails wheezing and a one plus pitting edema in lower extremities posterior tibial pulses were full and equal troponin and bnp levels were elevated and ekg showed a right bundle branch block with sinus tachycardia chest x-ray showed cardiomegaly and pulmonary edema and an echo showed a dilated left ventricle with an ejection fraction of thirty percent patient was diagnosed with myocarditis and will be admitted to telemetry patient will be placed on nasal cannula with two liters per minute of oxygen flow with oxygen stats being maintained above ninety six percent patient will continue taking her lisinopril as described as prescribed be given six hundred and twenty five milligrams of acetaminophen po q six hours for chest pain and iv furosemide forty milligrams q twelve hours for edema interventional cardiology infectious disease and radiology were consulted
